{meta: artist Vern Gosdin}
{meta: composer Vernon Gosdin and Max Duane Barnes}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]You ran crying to the bedroom
[F]I ran off to the bar
[G7]Another piece of heaven gone to [C]hell
[F]The words we spoke in anger just tore my world apart
[G7]And I sat there feeling sorry for [C]myself
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Then that old man sat down beside me
[F]And looked me in the eye
[G7]And said son I know what you're going [C]through
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
You ought to get down on your knees
[F]And thank [G7]your lucky stars that you got someone to go home [C]to
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[C7]You don't know about [F]lonely
[C]Or how long nights can be
[G7]Till you lived through the story
[C]That's still living in me
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
[C7]And you don't know about [F]sadness
[C]Till you faced life alone
[G7]You don't know about lonely
[C]Till it's chiseled in stone
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
So I brought these pretty flowers
[F]Hoping you would understand
[G7]Sometimes a man is such a [C]fool
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
Those golden words of wisdom
[F]From the heart of that old man
[G7]Showed me I ain't nothing without [C]you
{end_of_verse}

